## PRD Structure Standard

All PRDs must include these sections (can be TBD for drafts):

| Section | Requirement |
|---------|-------------|
| Status | Current PRD status (Drafting/Actionable/Closed/Abandoned) |
| Description | 1-3 line summary for quick context |
| Background | Context on why this project exists |
| DACE | Driver, Approver, Contributors, Escalation Path |
| Objectives | Customer statement and success metrics |
| Use Cases | In-scope and out-of-scope items |
| Requirements | Organized by milestone with priorities |
| Timeline | Milestones and expected delivery dates |
| Metrics | Learning agenda and success measures |
| Changelog | Record of changes with dates and authors |
